    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>THOUGHTS:</span><b>, By Hecubus</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Well, I've sit long enough without posting on this so here goes:  You do have to admit that with all but the mages FA Weapon done it does not seem up to par with the rest of them.  The 1200 damage is the same as our 49 Darkness spell as well as the duration being the same.  Seems to me like all of the other Epic Weapons proc/effect something that seems, well, Epic.  50+ kinda stuff.  I'm level 53 now and I still pull with engulfing darkness.   To be honest I've never even casted my 49 Darkness but a couple of times.  Fast cast time, low mana, and if it get's resisted (need I say more) you're not out that much mana and it won't take that long to cast it again.  I'd have to be level 60 Uber of Uber's to even take the time to THINK about starting this quest.  Stats are nice yeah.  That makes it attractive.  And just remember, not every necromancer in Norrath likes to solo 24/7, so quit thinking we do.  <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>URM WHY?!</span><b>, By Bethor whiterose</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I dont know where you get your ideas but a 1200 point dot in 1 min 36 seconds with a snare element on it?! This item is one of the best in the game as far as a necro is concerned, how many other items do you know with that kick ass 20 intel buff on it?!<BR>
Stop whining and using class envy as an excuse, this is undeniably the best necro weapon in the game. Just because it has a different proc on it doesn't make it lesser than the cleric weapon. Hell this thing would kill my ranger in short order if you used it properly.

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>UMM</span><b>, By Chekoff</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Anyone notice how the other epic caster weapons give the same critical stat? I.E. int or wis but all the ones I've seen have more mana added.... lets face it once you get to lvl 50+ you've probably got your int/wis to 200 and you will get a better boost from the mana then the int.  I know they could do lots of things to it and there would still be more that could be done but some extra points on the resists and 30 maybe or so extra mana would be helpful as well.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>AM I UBER?</span><b>, By Carsiven</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Almost every post that I have seen from fellow necros says that Cascading Darkness is resisted too much. I was wondering why people think this? I solo in Skyfire and almost never gotten a resist and when I do I run back to the pet and run in a circle and pet taunts off and I then have time for cascading (which I have never had resisted 2x on one mob).<BR> 
Some say it has a shorter duration but from what this web site says it has a longer duration, not only that it does a fair amount of dmg. The cost in mana is slightly more but the ratio is better than that of the lifetap line...which I also keep up constantly. I have probably only gotten somewhere around 5 cascading resistences. The only reason I can think of for this is that I have relatively high wisdom. This item I would use to pull for soloing, since the mobs in Skyfire arent exactly running around at SoW speed... I guess I'm the uber no resist necro.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>....</span><b>, By Anrath bonewraith</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Proc is completely UN epic. Period. I thought they were bringing up the items to be 'on par' with the cleric FA weapon. Well, they shafted necros yet again.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
